      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:6:1:2:2",
      "text": [
        " مِنْ سَعَادَةِ الرَّجُلِ أَنْ يَكُونَ لَهُ الْوَلَدُ يُعْرَفُ فِيهِ شِبْهُهُ خَلْقُهُ وَ خُلُقُهُ وَ شَمَائِلُهُ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from from his father, from Ibn Abu Umeyr, from Hisham Bin Al Musny, from Sudeyr, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Ja’far<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘From happiness of the man is that there happens to be for him the son in whom his resemblance would be recognised, in his appearance, and his mannerisms, and his virtues’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "2. Ali ibn Ibrahim has narrated from his father from ibn abu ‘Umayr from Hisham ibn al-Muthanna’ from Sadir who has said the following: “Abu Ja’far, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘It is of good fortune of a man to have a son who resembles his father, physically, morally and in his nature.”’ "
        ]
      }
    },
